snippets.title: DatasetService getDataset Sample
snippets.description: Returns the dataset specified by datasetID.

snippets.title: DatasetService insertDataset Sample
snippets.description: Creates a new empty dataset.

snippets.title: DatasetService patchDataset Sample
snippets.description: Updates information in an existing dataset. The update method replaces the entire dataset resource, whereas the patch method only replaces fields that are provided in the submitted dataset resource. This method supports RFC5789 patch semantics.

snippets.title: DatasetService updateDataset Sample
snippets.description: Updates information in an existing dataset. The update method replaces the entire dataset resource, whereas the patch method only replaces fields that are provided in the submitted dataset resource.

snippets.title: DatasetService deleteDataset Sample
snippets.description: Deletes the dataset specified by the datasetId value. Before you can delete a dataset, you must delete all its tables, either manually or by specifying deleteContents. Immediately after deletion, you can create another dataset with the same name.

snippets.title: DatasetService listDatasets Sample
snippets.description: Lists all datasets in the specified project to which the user has been granted the READER dataset role.

snippets.title: DatasetService undeleteDataset Sample
snippets.description: Undeletes a dataset which is within time travel window based on datasetId. If a time is specified, the dataset version deleted at that time is undeleted, else the last live version is undeleted.

snippets.title: DatasetService cancelJob Sample
snippets.description: Requests that a job be cancelled. This call will return immediately, and the client will need to poll for the job status to see if the cancel completed successfully. Cancelled jobs may still incur costs.

snippets.title: DatasetService getJob Sample
snippets.description: Returns information about a specific job. Job information is available for a six month period after creation. Requires that you're the person who ran the job, or have the Is Owner project role.

snippets.title: DatasetService insertJob Sample
snippets.description: Starts a new asynchronous job. This API has two different kinds of endpoint URIs, as this method supports a variety of use cases. * The *Metadata* URI is used for most interactions, as it accepts the job   configuration directly. * The *Upload* URI is ONLY for the case when you're sending both a load job   configuration and a data stream together.  In this case, the Upload URI   accepts the job configuration and the data as two distinct multipart MIME   parts.

snippets.title: DatasetService deleteJob Sample
snippets.description: Requests the deletion of the metadata of a job. This call returns when the job's metadata is deleted.

snippets.title: DatasetService listJobs Sample
snippets.description: Lists all jobs that you started in the specified project. Job information is available for a six month period after creation. The job list is sorted in reverse chronological order, by job creation time. Requires the Can View project role, or the Is Owner project role if you set the allUsers property.

snippets.title: DatasetService getQueryResults Sample
snippets.description: RPC to get the results of a query job.

snippets.title: DatasetService query Sample
snippets.description: Runs a BigQuery SQL query synchronously and returns query results if the query completes within a specified timeout.

snippets.title: DatasetService getModel Sample
snippets.description: Gets the specified model resource by model ID.

snippets.title: DatasetService listModels Sample
snippets.description: Lists all models in the specified dataset. Requires the READER dataset role. After retrieving the list of models, you can get information about a particular model by calling the models.get method.

snippets.title: DatasetService patchModel Sample
snippets.description: Patch specific fields in the specified model.

snippets.title: DatasetService deleteModel Sample
snippets.description: Deletes the model specified by modelId from the dataset.

snippets.title: DatasetService getServiceAccount Sample
snippets.description: RPC to get the service account for a project used for interactions with Google Cloud KMS

snippets.title: DatasetService getRoutine Sample
snippets.description: Gets the specified routine resource by routine ID.

snippets.title: DatasetService insertRoutine Sample
snippets.description: Creates a new routine in the dataset.

snippets.title: DatasetService updateRoutine Sample
snippets.description: Updates information in an existing routine. The update method replaces the entire Routine resource.

snippets.title: DatasetService patchRoutine Sample
snippets.description: Patches information in an existing routine. The patch method does a partial update to an existing Routine resource.

snippets.title: DatasetService deleteRoutine Sample
snippets.description: Deletes the routine specified by routineId from the dataset.

snippets.title: DatasetService listRoutines Sample
snippets.description: Lists all routines in the specified dataset. Requires the READER dataset role.

snippets.title: DatasetService listRowAccessPolicies Sample
snippets.description: Lists all row access policies on the specified table.

snippets.title: DatasetService getRowAccessPolicy Sample
snippets.description: Gets the specified row access policy by policy ID.

snippets.title: DatasetService createRowAccessPolicy Sample
snippets.description: Creates a row access policy.

snippets.title: DatasetService updateRowAccessPolicy Sample
snippets.description: Updates a row access policy.

snippets.title: DatasetService deleteRowAccessPolicy Sample
snippets.description: Deletes a row access policy.

snippets.title: DatasetService batchDeleteRowAccessPolicies Sample
snippets.description: Deletes provided row access policies.

snippets.title: DatasetService getTable Sample
snippets.description: Gets the specified table resource by table ID. This method does not return the data in the table, it only returns the table resource, which describes the structure of this table.

snippets.title: DatasetService insertTable Sample
snippets.description: Creates a new, empty table in the dataset.

snippets.title: DatasetService patchTable Sample
snippets.description: Updates information in an existing table. The update method replaces the entire table resource, whereas the patch method only replaces fields that are provided in the submitted table resource. This method supports RFC5789 patch semantics.

snippets.title: DatasetService updateTable Sample
snippets.description: Updates information in an existing table. The update method replaces the entire Table resource, whereas the patch method only replaces fields that are provided in the submitted Table resource.

snippets.title: DatasetService deleteTable Sample
snippets.description: Deletes the table specified by tableId from the dataset. If the table contains data, all the data will be deleted.

snippets.title: DatasetService listTables Sample
snippets.description: Lists all tables in the specified dataset. Requires the READER dataset role.
